# **üìå Project Brief ‚Äì Chatter Sales & Shift Management Web App for OnlyFans Agency**

## **1\. Overview & Goal**

Build a web-based internal application to manage:

* Chatter sales tracking (per shift, per creator)  
* Automatic commission calculation  
* Monthly performance dashboards  
* Shift scheduling with drag & drop  
* Role-based permissions (Admin, Chatter Manager, Chatter)

The app will be used daily by chatters, chatter managers, and admins to log sales, track performance, and manage work schedules.

Furthermore, it must be responsive for being used also from mobile. 

---

## **2\. Access & Authentication**

The app is accessible via subdomain:  
 **app.creatoradvisor.it**

* Login via email \+ password  
* Roles:  
  * **Admin**  
  * **Chatter Manager**  
  * **Chatter**

## **3\. Chatter Features**

### **3.1 Sales Entry (Per Shift)**

Each chatter can insert sales during their working shift. For each sale, the following fields are required:

* **Creator** (dropdown ‚Äì initially only: BIANCA, MELISA)  
* **Amount** (numeric, ‚Ç¨)  
* **Sale Type** (dropdown):  
  * CAM  
  * TIP  
  * PPV  
  * INITIAL  
* **Note** (optional text field)

#### **Timestamp rules:**

* By default, the **current time is auto-saved** (Italian timezone).  
* Chatter may backdate a sale:  
  * Backdated sales are automatically labeled as **OFFLINE**  
  * Real-time sales are labeled **ONLINE**

**![][image1]**

### **3.2 Sales Editing Rules**

* A chatter can edit **only their own sales**  
* Editing is allowed **within 24 hours**  
* After 24h ‚Üí **read-only**  
* Admin and Chatter Manager can always edit any sale

## **4\. Chatter Dashboard**

### **4.1 Monthly Performance Dashboard**

Automatically generated for the **current month**.

Includes:

üìà **Line Chart (Top)**

* Daily sales volume (day-by-day)

üìâ **Line Chart (Bottom)**

* Daily commissions generated

Side panel shows:

* **Total sales from beginning of the month**  
* **Total commissions generated (personal only). This is calculated as (sales\*% commission) \+ fixed salary (if any).**

‚ö†Ô∏è **Important rule:** Each chatter can only see **their own commissions and their sales**, never those of other chatters.

![][image2]

### **4.2 Sales Report Screen**

A separate page with a **detailed table of sales**.

Each row includes:

* Sale date & time  
* Chatter name  
* Sale type (CAM / TIP / PPV / CUSTOM / INITIAL)  
* Sale amount  
* Creator name  
* Status: **ONLINE / OFFLINE**

Filters (can be selected more filters at the same time):

* Date range  
* Creator  
* Sale type  
* Status (ONLINE / OFFLINE).

There must be the possibility to export the current selection in .CSV

## **5\. Shift Calendar**

A **monthly calendar view** showing work shifts. This section should be visible to all chatters.

Shifts are fixed time slots:

* **09:00 ‚Äì 14:30**  
* **14:30 ‚Äì 20:00**  
* **20:00 ‚Äì 01:00**

Features:

* Each chatter is represented by:  
  * Name  
  * Icon / avatar  
* **Drag & drop chatters between shifts**  
* Fully responsive (desktop \+ tablet)  
* The last row presents the chatters that are free on that day.

Permissions:

* Chatters ‚Üí view only  
* Chatter Managers & Admins ‚Üí can modify shifts

![][image4]

## **6\. Chatter Manager Features**

The **Chatter Manager** role sits between Admin and Chatter.

### **Capabilities:**

* Can view sales and reports for **all chatters**  
* Can **add, remove or edit any sale**, including:  
  * Amount  
  * Sale type  
  * Creator  
  * Timestamp  
  * Reassigning a sale to a different chatter (sales allocation correction)

* Can modify shifts:

  * Drag & drop chatters between shifts  
  * Make daily switches  
  * Adjust monthly calendar

### **Restrictions:**

* Cannot:  
  * Change commission percentages  
  * Change fixed salaries  
  * Invite or remove users  
  * Manage creators  
* Does **not** see other chatters‚Äô commission percentages (that are set by Admin only)

## **7\. Admin-Only Features**

### **7.1 Chatter Management**

Admin-only page to:

* Invite unlimited chatters  
* Required fields:  
  * Name  
  * Email  
  * Role (Chatter / Chatter Manager / Admin)

* System generates a **unique invitation link**  
* Chatter receives an email to:  
  * Set password  
  * Activate accoun

For each chatter, Admin can configure:

* **Commission percentage** (custom per chatter)  
* **Fixed salary**   
* **Identification photo**

---

### **7.2 Creator Management**

Admin-only page to manage creators.

Each creator has:

* **Name**  
* **Identification photo**  
* **Compensation**: Fixed salary cost (monthly amount), or Revenue share percentage (creator earning %). Only one compensation model can be active per creator at a time (salary or percentage).

Initial setup:

* MELISA (50%)  
* BIANCA (1000$ per month)

---

### **7.3 Admin Recap Dashboard**

Admin-only dashboard providing a **complete financial overview** of the agency‚Äôs performance.

The dashboard must display:

#### **1\. Global Metrics**

* **Total revenue per chatter** (sortable table or breakdown)  
* **Total commissions generated** (sum of all chatter commissions)  
* **Breakdown by creator** (each creator shown separately)  
* **Time scope selector**:  
  * Monthly view (selected month)  
  * Cumulative view (all-time totals)

**2\. Creator-Level Financial Breakdown**

For **each creator**, the dashboard must include a dedicated section with:

**Revenue & Earnings**

* Gross revenue generated by the creator in the given month (for now we cannot import it from OnlyFans so we will type it and save for every calendar month).  
* Creator earnings:  
  * Calculated either as a **percentage of revenue** *or*  
  * Based on a **fixed salary cost**, depending on the creator‚Äôs compensation model  
* Net revenue remaining after creator earnings

**Cost Rows (editable by Admin)**

* Marketing costs (for each creator)  
* Tool / software costs  
* Other optional operational costs 

**Agency Result**

* **Net agency profit per creator** for the selected period  
* Clear formula visibility (revenue ‚àí commissions ‚àí creator earnings ‚àí costs)
